WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.480
If you're looking to contribute to open source projects, I would start with projects that

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:09.320
you actually use and go on GitHub and take a look at their issue tracker.

00:00:09.320 --> 00:00:16.040
Maybe they have a label like good first issue or something mundane like a documentation

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:18.760
task or testing.

00:00:18.760 --> 00:00:23.400
Something small where you can get familiar with the contribution process.

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:28.360
If you're lucky, in a lot of projects, they will see that you're a new contributor and

00:00:28.360 --> 00:00:31.360
they'll give you advice about where you can go from there, but just getting your foot

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:36.320
in the door and getting up your first pull request will start the relationship and I'm

00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:40.160
sure that the other developers will be keen to help you out and give you some ideas from

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:40.919
where to go from there.

